ngaging in practices that do not diminish the earth's resources.FMarketing activities, such as developing a marketing strategy, do not occur separately from the rest of the company.TIf a company has multiple planning levels,the plans must be consistent and all must help achieve the overall goals of the corporation.When a consumer realizes there is a difference between their current state and their desired state, he/she has entered the _____ stage of the buying process.need recognition_____ combines the lifestyle traits of consumers and their personality styles with an analysis of their attitudes, activities, and values to determine groups of consumers with similar characteristics.PsychographicsProfessional buyers are shrewd and well informed.TB2B laws and regulations are often monitored by the DOD.FA subculture consists of a group of people who share the culture's beliefs and values.F_____ are the people and groups within the organization who actually utilize the product.UsersAs the demand for MP3 players increased, so did the demand for headphones. This is an example of _____.joint demandManufacturers and service providers are types of _____.producersThe shared beliefs, customs, behaviors, and attitudes of a society are known as _____.culture , cultureSelective perception isthe process of filtering out information based on how relevant it is to you.B2B markets differ from B2C markets becausesalespeople personally call on business customers to a far greater extent than they do consumers_____ refers to when people forget information, even if it is relevant to them.Selective retentionAll things being equal, companies want to do business with firms that are responsible.TAl manages a grocery store. He decided to put the bread on aisle 1 and the milk next to aisle 10. He is controlling his store's _____ to increase the time his customers spend in the store, which will hopefully result in more sales per customer.atmosphericsA(n) _____ outlines what the vendor is able to offer in terms of its product.RFPPurchasing agents for merchandisers are known asprofessional buyers.B2B markets tend to have shorter decision cycles than B2C markets.FBrands add value because they can save the consumer "search time" in addition to providing piece of mind for high-involvement products.TMarketers use different types of stimuli totry to make consumers more perceptive to their products.A _____ site is a site in which a business buys products from multiple sellers that go there to do business with the firm.buy side_____ involves tailoring a product so that it stands out from the competition and people want to buy it.PositioningPackaging can be part of the brand.TA brand is _____.a name, picture, design, or symbol used by a seller to differentiate their offeringsMarket managers can be found in which types of markets?consumer and B2BA(n) _____ is a characteristic of an offering.featureGoogle's AdSense and AdWords programs can be utilized by companies to aid in segmentation practices.TWhen Sally selected a group of upper income people living in Atlanta as her market, she was engaged in market segmentation.TThe four offering levels include all of the following EXCEPTthe product mix.Marketing of _____ items is often limited to simply trying to get the product in as many places as possible where a purchase could occur.convenience offerings_____ consist of final products that have been put together from raw materials, manufactured materials, and/or component parts.Original equipment manufacturing offeringsThis segmentation category answers the question, "How do my customers live their lives?"psychographicThe sub-segment of the Hispanic market that is characterized as containing individuals who are English dominant, free thinkers, and multicultural is known as _____.SYLrs_____ are characterized as being motivated by self-expression and tend to be young, enthusiastic, and compulsive consumers.ExperiencersThe total amount someone pays to own, use, and eventually dispose of a product is the TCO.TA brand extension involves the creation of a brand and then positioning it in the mind of the consumer.FForming close, personal relationships with customers and giving them exactly what they want is known as _____.one-to-one marketingFacilitating offerings are products and services a company purchases to support its operations but are not part of the firm's final product.TPepsi is an example of a(n) _____.brand nameThe number of different or distinct product lines offered by a company is known as _____.line breadthGeodemographics combines geographic and psychographic information for marketing purposes.FOfferings are _____.products and services designed to deliver value to customersA number of variations in a single product line is known as _____.line depthA company that produces laundry detergent offers one product with stain removing action while another is made for energy efficient washing machines. The company has utilized a _____ strategy.benefits segmentation_____ are often sold by distributors but a consumer can also buy many of the same products at a retail store.Maintenance, repair, operations offerings_____ are specialty items that are available only through limited channels.Specialty offeringsA _____ is the person responsible for all business decisions regarding offerings within one brand.brand managerAs companies do not want their products to be another "face in the crowd", marketers should be sure to _____ their product.positionAvoiding head-on competition with other firms trying to capture the same customers is one reason a firm may choose a _____ strategy.targeted marketingA benefit of utilizing a targeted marketing strategy is that a company may be able toretain "at risk" customers in danger of defecting to a competitor.A service is the tangible component of an offering.FA _____ is responsible for a broad group of offerings, such as home cleaning products, which have various brands within each group.category manager____